		"description": "This run takes in a CSV or JSON file of all the target offers to be created.\n\nExample offer:\n\n``` json\n{\n    \"title\": \"AT Instructor: HTML Code Offer - Yosemite National Park Hiking\",\n    \"content\": \"<h2 class=&#x27;preserveHtml&#x27; class=&#x27;preserveHtml&#x27; class=\\\\\\\"cmp-teaser__title\\\\\\\">\\\\n    Yosemite National Park Hiking\\\\n</h2>\\\\n<div class=&#x27;preserveHtml&#x27; class=&#x27;preserveHtml&#x27; class=\\\\\\\"cmp-teaser__description\\\\\\\">Take an unforgettable hiking adventure with WKND tour guides in Yosemite National Park!</div>\\\\n<div class=&#x27;preserveHtml&#x27; class=&#x27;preserveHtml&#x27; class=\\\\\\\"cmp-teaser__action-container\\\\\\\">\\\\n    <a class=&#x27;preserveHtml&#x27; class=&#x27;preserveHtml&#x27; class=\\\\\\\"cmp-teaser__action-link\\\\\\\" id=\\\\\\\"teaser-d9ec8d822c-cta-dca7e433ef\\\\\\\" data-cmp-clickable=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\n        href=\\\\\\\"/content/wknd/language-masters/en/adventures/yosemite-backpacking.html\\\\\\\">View\\\\n        Trip</a>\\\\n</div>\"\n}\n\n ```\n\nAn easy to use script to properly escape the `content` value is located: [https://git.corp.adobe.com/ADLS/mswuser-env/blob/dev/adobe-target/escapeOffers.js](https://git.corp.adobe.com/ADLS/mswuser-env/blob/dev/adobe-target/escapeOffers.js)",
